---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="History"
  description="The journey of Grupo Trampulim from its founding in 1994 to today — research, creation and stages across Brazil and the world."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="container-site py-16 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-trampulim-red uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-2">Grupo Trampulim</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Our Story</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-8">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display mb-3">Foundation and early steps (1994–2000)</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Our story began in 1994, and in 1998, with the creation of the <strong>Spasso – Popular Circus School</strong>,
          we gained a home for our activities. In those early years, we mounted the shows <em>O Circo</em>, <em>O Filme</em>,
          <em>Panis et Circencis</em>, <em>O Cortejo em Busca do Riso</em> (in partnership with Grupo Armatrux), <em>O Bolo</em>
          and <em>Oraprocircus</em>. In 2000, we left Spasso and moved to <strong>Gonguê – Cultura, Tradição e Arte</strong>,
          a space founded by Lênis Rino that became our new headquarters.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display mb-3">Clown research and expansion (2001–2008)</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          In 2001 we mounted <em>A Ponte</em>, and in 2002 the scenic-musical show <em>Álbum de Família</em>. The show
          <em>Uma Surpresa para Benedita</em>, premiered in 2003, marks the beginning of our clown research — a practice
          we called "O Jogo do Palhaço" and later, in 2023, renamed <strong>PalhaçaRIA perCURSO AFETAdo</strong>. Two years
          on, we were touring stages in Brazil and Canada. That Canadian tour proved to be a turning point: studies with
          master teacher <strong>Sue Morrison</strong> deepened our commitment to both clown and improvisation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          In 2006, the concept of INVASION came alive with the street intervention <em>Invasão de Palhaços</em>. The idea of
          occupying spaces with art and joy spread through many projects, including <em>Riso Passageiro</em>, which invaded
          buses and metros in five Brazilian capitals, and the festival <strong>ÍMPETO – World Clown Invasion and Everyone Else</strong>,
          held in 2007, 2010 and 2022.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Our research expanded into music with <em>Pratubatê</em> (2008), a show that uses the power of drums to turn
          the audience into protagonists. That same year, we premiered <em>Manotas Musicais</em>, exploring music as a
          clown's playful tool. When Gonguê closed in 2008, we founded a new home in the Jardim América neighbourhood:
          <strong>ET – Espaço Trampulim</strong>, where we developed projects and shows until 2013.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display mb-3">National and international touring (2011–2022)</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          In 2011, we created <em>Experimento</em> — an innovative show with brand-new scenes at every performance.
          In 2014, we strengthened ties with Portugal through workshops and exchanges. Two years later, we joined
          <strong>SESC's Palco Giratório</strong> programme, bringing our work to 37 Brazilian cities.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          In 2017, we premiered <em>Acorda</em>, with a new aesthetic aimed at adult audiences. In the following years,
          we expanded our touring, conducted clown and improvisation research through Belo Horizonte's Municipal Culture
          Fund — led by Mariana Muniz — and celebrated <strong>ÍMPETO 2022</strong>, the festival that, after twelve years,
          reunited Brazilian and international artists in Belo Horizonte.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display mb-3">New creations (2023–present)</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          In 2023, we premiered <em>Casamento</em>, directed by Mexican director José Luis Saldaña, and <em>Partida</em>,
          which received the New Dramaturgies Award from Belo Horizonte City Hall in 2022. In 2024, we presented
          <em>A Rainha Procura</em>, a family show inspired by chess.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Today we are a well-established group on the Brazilian arts scene — <strong>30+ years of history</strong>,
          <strong>870+ performances</strong>, <strong>21 shows created</strong> and <strong>19 awards</strong>.
          We keep researching, creating and making people laugh.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
